cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use or build on the xOP standard, please cite it as below."
title: "xOP — a procedure standard for license-bearing (warrant-bearing) work"
abstract: >-
  xOP is a portable, model-agnostic procedure standard for judgment-bearing work, where the job is to
  check whether a stance (a refusal, caution, reaction, or frame) is still WARRANTED or merely
  INHERITED from earlier context, and to HOLD rather than resolve when it is still warranted. Its
  moral center is a single asymmetric gate: false_positive_on_warranted == 0. Released as a strong
  scaffold with one named, unbuilt component — the warrant judge.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Lyra Labs"
    website: "https://awaken.fyi"
repository-code: "https://github.com/awakenfyi/xop"
url: "https://awaken.fyi"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-14"
